{"version":"1.2","person":{"datePublished":"2023-11-08","name":"Richard de Acton","nameForms":[{"lang":"en","fullText":"Richard de Acton","parts":[{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Given","value":"Richard"},{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Surname","value":"de Acton"}],"order":"EUROTYPIC"}],"alternateName":"Richard de Acton","gender":"Male","lifespan":"1297–1342","fullLifespan":"1297–1342","birthDate":"+1297","birthPlace":{"address":"Newcastle upon Tyne, Northumberland, England","geo":{"latitude":54.9714,"longitude":-1.614,"@type":"GeoCoordinates"},"@type":"Place"},"deathDate":"+1342","deathPlace":{"address":"Hexham, Northumberland, England","geo":{"latitude":54.9718,"longitude":-2.1048,"@type":"GeoCoordinates"},"@type":"Place"},"userCertifiedLifeSummary":"«b»Biography«/b»\nRichard de Acton was the son of Richard de Acton of Newcastle (fl. 1333/4). He was the brother of Nicholas de Acton (fl. 1333/4, dsp), who was married to one Alice [____] (dsp).\n\nRichard was the first husband of Maud de Emeldon (d. 08 Sep 1369), who remarried to Sir Alexander de Hilton. She outlived both husbands, her brother-in-law Nicholas de Acton and his wife, as well as her daughter Elizabeth Acton. The family estates inevitably fell to the children of their daughter Elizabeth.","events":[{"name":"Birth","sources":"0","year":"1297","date":"1297","place":"Newcastle upon Tyne, Northumberland, England"},{"name":"Death","sources":"0","year":"1342","date":"1342","place":"Hexham, Northumberland, England","age":"45"}],"parent":[{"name":"Richard de Acton","gender":"Male","lifespan":"1282–1342","birthDate":"A+1282","deathDate":"/+1342-05-17","age":60,"@type":"Person","identifier":"L5PG-59N","url":"https://ancestors.familysearch.org/en/L5PG-59N/richard-de-acton-1282-1342","published":true}],"sibling":[{"name":"Richard de Acton","gender":"Male","lifespan":"1297–1342","birthDate":"+1297","deathDate":"+1342","age":45,"@type":"Person","identifier":"LWFF-858","url":"https://ancestors.familysearch.org/en/LWFF-858/ri